President Barack Obama has written a letter to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate, stating that the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13712, regarding the situation in Burundi, will continue beyond November 22, 2016. The situation in Burundi is characterized by violence against civilians, unrest, incitement of violence, and political repression, which poses a threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. Therefore, President Obama has determined it necessary to extend the national emergency.